## Typography

### UIKText — always use instead of raw `Text`

```dart
UIKText.pageTitle('Dashboard')
UIKText.pageSubtitle('Overview')
UIKText.h1('Section Header')
UIKText.h2('...')
UIKText.h3('...')
UIKText.h4('...')
UIKText.h5('...')
UIKText.h6('...')
UIKText.body('Regular paragraph text')
UIKText.small('Caption or metadata')
```

### Optional parameters (all constructors)

```dart
UIKText.body(
  'Truncated description',
  color: Colors.grey,       // overrides theme color only
  textAlign: TextAlign.center,
  maxLines: 2,              // adds TextOverflow.ellipsis automatically
  overflow: TextOverflow.fade,
)
```

### Rules

- Never use `Text(...)` directly in feature UI — always use `UIKText`.
- Never hardcode a `TextStyle` inline. If a style isn't covered by `UIKText`, add it to `DesignTokens` and `ThemeData` extension first.
- Color overrides should only be used for one-off semantic exceptions (e.g. error red, muted grey). If the same override appears in 2+ places, add a named style.

