## Bottom Sheets

### UIKitBottomSheet.show — standard sheet

```dart
// Content only, no footer
UIKitBottomSheet.show(
  context,
  title: 'Filters',
  content: FiltersWidget(),
);

// Single primary action
UIKitBottomSheet.show(
  context,
  title: 'Confirm',
  content: ConfirmWidget(),
  primaryAction: BottomSheetAction(
    label: 'Confirm',
    onTap: () async => confirm(),
  ),
);

// Primary + secondary (cancel)
UIKitBottomSheet.show(
  context,
  title: 'Delete item',
  content: DeleteWarning(),
  primaryAction: BottomSheetAction(label: 'Delete', onTap: () async => delete()),
  secondaryAction: BottomSheetAction(label: 'Cancel', onTap: () async => cancel()),
);

// Custom footer
UIKitBottomSheet.show(
  context,
  title: 'Pick a plan',
  content: PlanPicker(),
  footer: PlanFooterWidget(),
);
```

### UIKitBottomSheet.showPaged — multi-step flows

```dart
UIKitBottomSheet.showPaged(
  context,
  pages: [
    BottomSheetPage(
      title: 'Step 1',
      content: Step1Widget(),
      primaryAction: BottomSheetAction(
        label: 'Next',
        onTap: () async => BottomSheetPage.pushNext(context, step2),
      ),
    ),
    BottomSheetPage(
      title: 'Step 2',
      content: Step2Widget(),
      primaryAction: BottomSheetAction(label: 'Finish', onTap: () async => finish()),
    ),
  ],
);
```

Navigating pages from inside content:

```dart
// Push next page
BottomSheetPage.pushNext(context, nextPage);

// Go back
BottomSheetPage.popPage(context);
```

### Rules

- Never pass both `footer` and `primaryAction` — this will throw an assertion error.
- `secondaryAction` is only valid alongside `primaryAction`. It renders as a ghost button below the primary.
- `footer` is for fully custom layouts only. Prefer `primaryAction` / `secondaryAction` for standard CTAs so styling stays consistent.
- Never call `Navigator.pop()` inside a bottom sheet — always use `FamilyModalSheet.of(context).popPage()` or `BottomSheetPage.popPage(context)`.
- Never use raw `showModalBottomSheet` or `showBottomSheet` in feature code. Exception: `UIKitBottomSheet.showExpandable()` for drag-to-expand content sheets (Maps/Spotify-style).

### Scroll behaviour

- Content scrolls automatically when it overflows 60% of screen height — no manual configuration needed.
- `GradientFade` is applied automatically at the bottom edge when content is scrollable.
- For long lists inside a sheet, wrap in a `SizedBox` with an explicit height rather than relying on the overflow detector — it will be more performant.

### GradientFade — standalone use

```dart
GradientFade(
  fadeTop: false,
  fadeBottom: true,
  fadeHeight: 40,
  // color defaults to Theme.of(context).colorScheme.surface
  child: myScrollableList,
)
```

